Entity relatedness is topic with much history in data mining, and a wide range of text-based, graph-based, and embedding-based similarity measures exists (see Section (ref) and e.g., [witten2008effective,entity-relatedness]). 
Similarly, recall can be quantified in a variety of ways, for instance, via the number of statements, predicates, inlinks, outlinks, etc. We shall now see different approaches to both problems.